00:34:24.330 --> 00:34:26.030
Get back to it.

00:34:26.030 --> 00:34:27.410
Let's go.

00:34:27.410 --> 00:34:31.450
♫ Our family puppy, Bbobbi ♫

00:34:33.550 --> 00:34:34.740
Should I switch the PR Team Leader?

00:34:34.740 --> 00:34:35.940
Just leave him.

00:34:35.940 --> 00:34:39.640
He works harder than the other losers.

00:34:43.450 --> 00:34:45.290
What?

00:34:45.290 --> 00:34:46.950
I need to get back to the center.

00:34:46.950 --> 00:34:49.150
Is it something I need to know about?

00:34:49.150 --> 00:34:50.580
I'll take care of it myself.

00:34:50.580 --> 00:34:52.590
Okay. Work hard.

00:34:52.590 --> 00:34:53.870
Yes, sir.

00:34:58.590 --> 00:34:59.790
[Mr. Im at Lucid Club]

00:34:59.790 --> 00:35:01.380
[A traffic cop came in, and he's making a scene]

00:35:02.620 --> 00:35:03.710
Hyungnim,

00:35:03.710 --> 00:35:06.320
the crazy bastard is searching
the parking lot, not the rooms.

00:35:06.320 --> 00:35:08.560
- Parking lot?
- Yes.

00:35:25.330 --> 00:35:26.920
What's this about?

00:35:27.940 --> 00:35:31.010
I'm looking for a car. It doesn't seem to be here.

00:35:32.220 --> 00:35:33.960
What car?

00:35:35.930 --> 00:35:39.230
I looked up the registration. It belongs here.

00:35:39.230 --> 00:35:40.980
2668.

00:35:43.180 --> 00:35:45.820
Please leave since you checked.

00:35:48.460 --> 00:35:50.710
You can't crumple it. Geez.

00:35:50.710 --> 00:35:52.530
It's all crumpled up.

00:35:52.530 --> 00:35:54.160
Seriously.

00:35:54.160 --> 00:35:55.600
But you aren't asking why I'm looking for it.

00:35:55.600 --> 00:35:58.380
I'm not curious. Get lost.

00:35:58.380 --> 00:36:01.960
Looks like you don't want to know about it.

00:36:01.960 --> 00:36:05.810
To make it clear, it was parked illegally.

00:36:07.660 --> 00:36:09.810
At Obong Intersection a month ago.

00:36:10.790 --> 00:36:15.080
It was in front of a fried chicken
shop nearby. Does it ring a bell?

00:36:15.080 --> 00:36:16.330
What are you trying to do?

00:36:16.330 --> 00:36:18.120
What do you think? I'm working.

00:36:18.120 --> 00:36:21.780
Yes, the suspect lineup is right here.

00:36:21.780 --> 00:36:24.520
Attention. Okay.

00:36:25.320 --> 00:36:27.150
Let's see.

00:36:28.430 --> 00:36:30.020
Okay.

00:36:32.140 --> 00:36:34.850
- Let's see.
- You crazy bastard.

00:36:40.630 --> 00:36:42.410
Stop that.

00:36:51.260 --> 00:36:53.100
Here.

00:36:53.100 --> 00:36:55.460
Call me if you find it.

00:36:55.460 --> 00:36:57.170
[Dokgo Cheol]

00:37:02.380 --> 00:37:04.020
He's here.

00:37:14.496 --> 00:37:15.450
What happened?

00:37:15.450 --> 00:37:17.320
I found the company that got
the broker a burner phone.

00:37:17.320 --> 00:37:19.590
But we found someone unexpected.

00:37:19.590 --> 00:37:23.580
Gwak Jeong Do. Gwak Jeong Do.

00:37:23.580 --> 00:37:24.700
That sounds familiar.

00:37:24.700 --> 00:37:26.550
Four previous convictions. The latest one
was an aggravated assault.

00:37:26.550 --> 00:37:28.890
Right. Gwak Jeong Do of Silver Ax Gang, right?

00:37:28.890 --> 00:37:32.070
He's currently at Pilseung Gang.

00:37:32.070 --> 00:37:33.810
Pilseung Gang?

00:37:34.720 --> 00:37:36.750
Pilseung Gang...

00:37:36.750 --> 00:37:38.570
You mean Ju Seung Pil?

00:37:53.080 --> 00:37:55.770
It's not a formal gathering. Smile a bit.

00:37:55.770 --> 00:37:57.600
You know what I mean, right?

00:38:42.860 --> 00:38:44.820
Are you looking for something?

00:38:44.820 --> 00:38:48.060
Well, I need to use the restroom.

00:38:48.060 --> 00:38:49.760
There's one in the room.

00:38:49.760 --> 00:38:51.710
Oh, right.

00:38:51.710 --> 00:38:53.760
But it's for No. 2.

00:38:53.760 --> 00:38:55.990
- Oh, No. 2.
- Yes.

00:38:55.990 --> 00:38:58.890
It's to the right at the end of the hallway.

00:38:58.890 --> 00:39:01.520
- Okay, thank you.
- Sure.

00:39:17.550 --> 00:39:19.790
This isn't the parking lot.

00:39:20.840 --> 00:39:22.840
Are you lost or...

00:39:22.840 --> 00:39:25.070
did you intend to be here?

00:39:25.070 --> 00:39:27.020
This isn't it.

00:39:27.020 --> 00:39:29.540
Well, I needed to use the restroom.

00:39:29.540 --> 00:39:32.700
Why is this building so huge?

00:39:32.700 --> 00:39:34.080
Take him there.

00:39:34.080 --> 00:39:35.430
Yes, sir.

00:39:36.850 --> 00:39:38.270
Good day.

00:39:41.940 --> 00:39:43.520
Shouldn't we take care of him?

00:39:43.520 --> 00:39:45.300
Leave him.

00:39:45.300 --> 00:39:47.260
Let him control the traffic.

00:39:59.140 --> 00:40:00.170
Unni.

00:40:00.170 --> 00:40:02.010
Unni, are you okay?

00:40:02.010 --> 00:40:03.430
Gosh...

00:40:04.740 --> 00:40:06.420
What happened?

00:40:06.420 --> 00:40:08.020
Gosh, Unni...

00:40:08.020 --> 00:40:10.910
You passed out while shooting.

00:40:10.910 --> 00:40:12.320
Don't get up yet.

00:40:12.320 --> 00:40:14.100
I didn't even push you hard.

00:40:14.100 --> 00:40:17.000
Geez! You almost killed her on set. You idiot.

00:40:17.000 --> 00:40:18.250
- It hurts.
- Does it?

00:40:18.250 --> 00:40:20.150
How could you say that in front of Unni?

00:40:20.150 --> 00:40:22.000
It's not Nam Ju's fault.

00:40:22.000 --> 00:40:25.450
Didn't you have a concussion on set
because he pushed you?

00:40:25.450 --> 00:40:29.190
I had a flash of memory in that moment.

00:40:30.170 --> 00:40:34.110
And I got dizzy and fainted, I think.

00:40:34.110 --> 00:40:37.540
The doctor didn't think it was
due to an external shock.

00:40:37.540 --> 00:40:39.810
See? You owe me.

00:40:39.810 --> 00:40:41.630
You got your memory back
because I pushed you, right?

00:40:41.630 --> 00:40:44.980
Gosh, Unni. What memory is it?

00:40:45.820 --> 00:40:47.510
More importantly,

00:40:48.640 --> 00:40:51.270
I want to ask you something.

00:40:52.330 --> 00:40:54.650
M-Me?

00:40:59.600 --> 00:41:01.730
Unni, drink this.

00:41:08.670 --> 00:41:10.980
Don't trust anyone yet.

00:41:10.980 --> 00:41:13.560
No matter how close you are,

00:41:13.560 --> 00:41:16.080
don't trust anyone until you
get your memory back.

00:41:16.080 --> 00:41:18.490
Anyone could be a culprit.

00:41:19.830 --> 00:41:23.870
Since I met you, I've wanted to ask you something.

00:41:23.870 --> 00:41:27.110
You can ask me anything. What is it?

00:41:28.190 --> 00:41:32.060
Why was I alone that day?

00:41:32.060 --> 00:41:33.170
Huh?

00:41:33.170 --> 00:41:37.150
Twenty-five years ago,
on the day I had the accident.

00:41:37.150 --> 00:41:42.180
You mean, the day you won the Best Actress award?

00:41:42.180 --> 00:41:45.530
Not others, but you were always by my side.

00:41:45.530 --> 00:41:48.480
You even went to the restroom with me.

00:41:48.480 --> 00:41:51.380
Why was I alone then?

00:41:52.800 --> 00:41:55.130
To be honest, that day...

00:41:55.130 --> 00:41:56.260
[Im Se Ra]

00:41:56.260 --> 00:42:00.000
I was about to go to the van
with the bouquets at the green room.

00:42:00.000 --> 00:42:02.440
Tae Suk, hold on.

00:42:03.570 --> 00:42:07.350
We're having a surprise party
at Se Ra's place today.

00:42:07.350 --> 00:42:08.430
Surprise party?

00:42:08.430 --> 00:42:11.450
Yes. So, you should drive separately.

00:42:11.450 --> 00:42:12.600
Am I preparing it?

00:42:12.600 --> 00:42:16.000
Yes. Make it look pretty.

00:42:16.000 --> 00:42:18.940
Unni will be so surprised.

00:42:20.690 --> 00:42:23.700
She can start a flower shop.

00:42:23.700 --> 00:42:26.560
Since there'll be a surprise party at your place,

00:42:26.560 --> 00:42:29.210
I was told to drive separately and prepare it.

00:42:29.210 --> 00:42:31.110
I thought everyone else was in the van.

00:42:31.110 --> 00:42:34.560
I had no idea you were on it alone.

00:42:34.560 --> 00:42:37.690
I was happily preparing
for the party at your place.

00:42:37.690 --> 00:42:39.170
But on TV...

00:42:39.170 --> 00:42:40.480
This morning, after the award ceremony...

00:42:40.480 --> 00:42:43.800
when there was breaking news
about your accident, I...

00:42:43.800 --> 00:42:46.820
I was so shocked.

00:42:46.820 --> 00:42:49.010
Due to the accident...

00:42:49.010 --> 00:42:52.530
My sister must've been there, too.

00:42:52.530 --> 00:42:55.210
Yes, your sister, Baek Ja?

00:43:01.560 --> 00:43:03.180
Baek Ja.

00:43:19.240 --> 00:43:22.220
What did you remember earlier, by the way?

00:43:22.220 --> 00:43:25.470
You said you remembered right before the accident.

00:43:25.470 --> 00:43:28.990
About a month ago, right before the accident,

00:43:28.990 --> 00:43:31.430
I think I met someone.

00:43:31.430 --> 00:43:32.970
Who?

00:43:34.830 --> 00:43:38.420
I don't know since I lost that memory.

00:43:38.420 --> 00:43:41.840
But he was wearing a watch.

00:43:41.840 --> 00:43:43.920
A-A watch?

00:43:45.010 --> 00:43:47.670
It's your fault! It's your fault!

00:43:53.040 --> 00:43:55.740
I remember because it was an unusual watch.

00:43:56.500 --> 00:43:59.890
It's definitely the same watch I saw then.

00:44:06.220 --> 00:44:09.650
You mean, the man from 25 years ago reappeared?

00:44:09.650 --> 00:44:11.060
But why?

00:44:11.060 --> 00:44:15.170
I got into the accident after
I met him 25 years ago, too.

00:44:15.170 --> 00:44:17.340
Same with this time.

00:44:17.340 --> 00:44:18.780
What does that mean?

00:44:18.780 --> 00:44:22.130
It means he might be the one who did this to you.

00:44:22.130 --> 00:44:25.010
Who's that crazy bastard, anyway?

00:44:25.010 --> 00:44:26.820
I should look for him.

00:44:26.820 --> 00:44:27.850
How would you?

00:44:27.850 --> 00:44:30.190
You have no memory. You don't even know his name.

00:44:30.190 --> 00:44:33.020
Thankfully, there's someone who might know him.

00:44:33.020 --> 00:44:35.270
Gosh, who?

00:44:36.780 --> 00:44:38.510
Kang Du Won.

00:44:42.510 --> 00:44:45.550
- I'll get going now. Bye.
- Wait...

00:44:45.550 --> 00:44:48.090
Unni, Unni, Unni!

00:44:48.090 --> 00:44:49.840
You're going now? Go later.

00:44:49.840 --> 00:44:51.380
I don't have time to waste.

00:44:51.380 --> 00:44:53.470
Go with that manager, then.

00:44:53.470 --> 00:44:54.510
Manager?

00:44:54.510 --> 00:44:57.530
The manager who came with you. Dokgo Cheol.

00:45:01.980 --> 00:45:03.650
Who are you?

00:45:04.900 --> 00:45:08.030
I'm sorry. I think I got the wrong room.

00:45:11.500 --> 00:45:13.000
[VIP Room]

00:45:16.000 --> 00:45:19.000
Excuse me, when did you get hospitalized?

00:45:19.000 --> 00:45:21.070
Two days ago.

00:45:21.070 --> 00:45:23.480
Oh, I see.

00:45:27.800 --> 00:45:31.140
Excuse me, when did the car accident victim at

00:45:31.140 --> 00:45:33.340
the VIP room get discharged?

00:45:34.980 --> 00:45:37.010
He left three days ago.

00:45:37.010 --> 00:45:38.910
He was planning to have a long-term stay,

00:45:38.910 --> 00:45:42.030
but he suddenly wanted to be discharged.

00:45:42.030 --> 00:45:43.370
I see.

00:45:49.410 --> 00:45:52.600
The number you dialed does not exist.

00:45:52.600 --> 00:45:55.790
Please check and dial again.

00:45:55.790 --> 00:45:58.090
I looked up the person you mentioned.

00:45:58.090 --> 00:46:00.950
They didn't just change the number.
They got rid of the phone.

00:46:00.950 --> 00:46:02.930
They didn't get a new number at all.

00:46:02.930 --> 00:46:06.010
They must've switched to a burner phone.

00:46:06.010 --> 00:46:07.020
Anyway, thank you.

00:46:07.020 --> 00:46:10.090
Check their address and text it to me.

00:46:11.260 --> 00:46:12.770
He's busy.

00:46:12.770 --> 00:46:14.260
Why would a manager be busy?

00:46:14.260 --> 00:46:16.120
This is what managers are for.

00:46:16.120 --> 00:46:19.790
And Kang Du Won won't meet you
just because you went there.

00:46:19.790 --> 00:46:22.630
There's no way he'd refuse to see Im Se Ra.

00:46:22.630 --> 00:46:24.870
Okay. Come with me, then.

00:46:24.870 --> 00:46:27.380
No. You've done enough for me already.

00:46:27.380 --> 00:46:30.340
- It's okay. I'll go.
- Wait...

00:46:30.340 --> 00:46:31.560
What?

00:46:32.360 --> 00:46:34.030
Yes, hello?

00:46:34.030 --> 00:46:36.280
Where are you? Come right now.

00:46:36.280 --> 00:46:38.460
Where are you? I'm at C.

00:46:38.460 --> 00:46:39.890
How many times did I tell you?

00:46:39.890 --> 00:46:41.200
Huh?

00:46:41.200 --> 00:46:43.420
Mr. Dokgo!

00:46:43.420 --> 00:46:44.590
It's you.

00:46:44.590 --> 00:46:46.250
My gosh. Hello.

00:46:46.250 --> 00:46:49.490
- Hello.
- How did you know? What a relief.

00:46:49.490 --> 00:46:51.970
Pardon? I'm here for work.

00:46:51.970 --> 00:46:54.520
Right. You didn't come because Unni called.

00:46:54.520 --> 00:46:56.500
- What do I do?
- Call about what?

00:46:56.500 --> 00:47:00.750
Unni left to meet her old
road manager, CEO Kang Du Won.

00:47:00.750 --> 00:47:03.510
Kang Du Won. Why all of a sudden?

00:47:03.510 --> 00:47:05.930
It's too complicated to explain. It's urgent.

00:47:05.930 --> 00:47:07.400
You must know, too.

00:47:07.400 --> 00:47:09.690
He owns Two One, the biggest
entertainment company in the country.

00:47:09.690 --> 00:47:11.650
Two One Entertainment?

00:47:14.760 --> 00:47:17.790
Come on. Don't just say I can't.

00:47:17.790 --> 00:47:20.530
Let CEO Kang Du Won know.

00:47:20.530 --> 00:47:23.070
Call him first and come back.

00:47:23.070 --> 00:47:25.090
I'd call him if I could reach him.

00:47:25.090 --> 00:47:27.420
I called the office, but they won't
connect him to me.

00:47:27.420 --> 00:47:29.390
How am I supposed to call him?

00:47:29.390 --> 00:47:31.480
If you keep insisting like this,

00:47:31.480 --> 00:47:33.110
we'll have to follow the law.

00:47:33.110 --> 00:47:34.550
That's great.

00:47:34.550 --> 00:47:37.380
I know a cop, too.

00:47:43.250 --> 00:47:45.510
- Hey, ahjumma!
- Let go!

00:47:49.110 --> 00:47:52.670
Geez. You're making a mistake.

00:47:57.540 --> 00:48:00.290
She actually hurt her head while shooting.

00:48:00.290 --> 00:48:02.070
I guess she remembered something.

00:48:02.070 --> 00:48:03.090
It sounded like an important memory.

00:48:03.090 --> 00:48:06.230
She went to see CEO Kang to confirm it.

00:48:19.040 --> 00:48:20.440
[Two One's Kang Du Won leading
the entertainment industry]

00:48:33.980 --> 00:48:36.630
Come on.

00:48:36.630 --> 00:48:39.960
I'm begging you for a reason.

00:48:39.960 --> 00:48:43.770
I told you Du Won and I are very close.

00:48:43.770 --> 00:48:44.900
If he knew I was here,

00:48:44.900 --> 00:48:47.810
he'd be running out of there barefoot.

00:48:47.810 --> 00:48:51.250
Begging won't work in this situation.

00:48:51.250 --> 00:48:55.360
Gosh, whatever. I'll lie down here. Whatever.

00:48:56.470 --> 00:48:59.340
The police will be here in
five minutes once we call.

00:48:59.340 --> 00:49:00.500
Don't cause a scene and-

00:49:00.500 --> 00:49:02.710
Here's a police officer.

00:49:02.710 --> 00:49:04.680
They came already?

00:49:25.680 --> 00:49:26.840
She's not trespassing.

00:49:26.840 --> 00:49:29.260
I can vouch for her.

00:49:30.640 --> 00:49:32.220
Seeing CEO Kang without an appointment-

00:49:32.220 --> 00:49:34.390
Call him for her first.

00:49:34.390 --> 00:49:38.230
He'll decide whether to see her or not.

00:49:45.230 --> 00:49:47.360
Thank you for helping me.

00:49:47.360 --> 00:49:48.710
Don't thank me.

00:49:48.710 --> 00:49:51.290
I came to tend to a business, too.

00:49:51.290 --> 00:49:53.900
What business do you have here?

00:50:11.360 --> 00:50:15.050
The mighty Im Se Ra gets nervous, too.

00:50:15.050 --> 00:50:17.520
Nervous?

00:50:17.520 --> 00:50:20.960
The CEO here used to work for me.

00:50:20.960 --> 00:50:25.340
He couldn't even look me in the eye. Come on.

00:50:26.590 --> 00:50:29.750
I suppose. The junior detective
couldn't even look at you.

00:50:29.750 --> 00:50:31.560
I'm sure the road manager couldn't, either.

00:50:31.560 --> 00:50:34.550
I wonder if he could've even talked to you alone.

00:50:34.550 --> 00:50:39.330
Are you doing this because I called
you a manager last time?

00:50:40.410 --> 00:50:41.890
- What?
- It must be.

00:50:41.890 --> 00:50:44.140
You've been sarcastic with me since then.

00:50:44.140 --> 00:50:47.500
How could a mere detective
be sarcastic with a goddess?

00:50:47.500 --> 00:50:49.000
That would be out of question.

00:50:49.000 --> 00:50:52.190
Gosh, I made a great mistake.

00:50:52.190 --> 00:50:54.400
I apologize for calling you a manager.

00:50:54.400 --> 00:50:56.160
I'm sorry. Happy now?

00:50:56.160 --> 00:50:57.730
Whatever.

00:50:58.500 --> 00:51:00.070
Don't ever become my manager.

00:51:00.070 --> 00:51:01.510
Don't even say you will.

00:51:01.510 --> 00:51:03.910
I refuse.

00:51:03.910 --> 00:51:06.770
Be clear. I said no first, not you.

00:51:06.770 --> 00:51:08.580
Even if you begged me,

00:51:08.580 --> 00:51:10.660
I'll say "No, thank you."

00:51:10.660 --> 00:51:13.850
I won't do it even if you begged me.

00:51:15.720 --> 00:51:17.890
He's so petty.

00:51:28.770 --> 00:51:30.610
Is she an actor you like?

00:51:30.610 --> 00:51:33.820
Who's she? I've seen her somewhere.

00:51:33.820 --> 00:51:36.910
She's an actor. You must've seen her on TV.

00:52:06.590 --> 00:52:12.910
[Jewelry Shop Girl]

00:52:17.170 --> 00:52:20.060
When you wake up after an endoscopy,

00:52:21.200 --> 00:52:26.390
you realize a lot of time has passed.

00:52:26.390 --> 00:52:30.150
That's how it felt when I woke up at the hospital.

00:52:30.150 --> 00:52:33.590
All I did was close my eyes and open them again.

00:52:34.590 --> 00:52:37.010
I haven't changed.

00:52:38.720 --> 00:52:42.140
Without achieving anything,

00:52:42.140 --> 00:52:48.090
I only aged and turned into who I am now.

00:53:00.220 --> 00:53:02.160
He's waiting for you.

00:53:17.430 --> 00:53:20.280
Wow, is this really Im Se Ra?

00:53:20.280 --> 00:53:23.150
Wow. You became so pretty.

00:53:23.150 --> 00:53:25.470
I almost...

00:53:25.470 --> 00:53:27.520
I almost didn't recognize you.

00:53:27.520 --> 00:53:30.850
Come here. How long has it been? Come here.

00:53:32.760 --> 00:53:34.380
I came to check something.

00:53:34.380 --> 00:53:35.730
Let me go first.

00:53:35.730 --> 00:53:37.450
I was actually going to meet you.

00:53:37.450 --> 00:53:38.990
Although you beat me to it.

00:53:38.990 --> 00:53:40.530
Me?

00:53:41.650 --> 00:53:43.130
Why?

00:53:46.300 --> 00:53:49.070
I want to talk privately.

